    • Method Detail

      • getHomePosition

        com.kuka.device.common.JointPosition getHomePosition()
        Returns the home position of this joint device. The home position is a user-defined joint position.
        Returns:
        The home position of this joint device.

      • setHomePosition

        void setHomePosition(com.kuka.geometry.Frame home,
                     com.kuka.geometry.LoadData loadData)
        Sets the home position of this joint device. A unique joint position is calculated in such a way that the robot's flange is positioned on the given frame, even if the frame was originally touched up with a tool center point different from the flange. The conversion requires that redundancy information be available for this frame. If no redundancy information is available, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.

        For more control, use setHomePosition(JointPosition) and do the calculation using IKinematicsCalculator.getInverseKinematicsFromFrameAndRedundancy(Frame, LoadData).

        Parameters:
        home - A frame with redundancy information (e.g. a taught frame) defining the new home position.
        loadData - Description of load attached to the flange. This load data is used in the kinematics calculation. However, it only has an effect if absolute accuracy is available for this robot.

      • setHomePosition

        void setHomePosition(com.kuka.device.common.JointPosition homePosition)
        Sets the home position of this joint device.
        Parameters:
        homePosition - The new home position of this joint device. The amount of values must match the joint count of this joint device. Otherwise an exception will be thrown.

      • isInHome

        boolean isInHome()
        Returns true if the joint device is in its home position, i.e. its commanded joint position is close to the home position, and false otherwise.
        Returns:
        True if the joint device is in its home position, and false otherwise.
